<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idef8414cf-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9" identifier="/us/usc/t7/s2482"><num value="2482">§ 2482.</num><heading> How issued</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A certificate of plant variety protection shall be issued in the name of the United States of America under the seal of the Plant Variety Protection Office, and shall be signed by the Secretary or have the signature of the Secretary placed thereon, and shall be recorded in the Plant Variety Protection Office.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idef8414d0-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/577/tII/s82">Pub. L. 91–577, title II, § 82</ref>, <date date="1970-12-24">Dec. 24, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1551">84 Stat. 1551</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/103/349/s13">Pub. L. 103–349, § 13</ref>(<i>l</i>), <date date="1994-10-06">Oct. 6, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/3143">108 Stat. 3143</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idef8414d1-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idef8414d2-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idef8414d3-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1994—<ref href="/us/pl/103/349">Pub. L. 103–349</ref> substituted “the signature of the Secretary” for “his signature”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idef8414d4-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idef8414d5-3a6e-11f1-addd-bbaf0b3f68e9"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1994 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/103/349">Pub. L. 103–349</ref> effective 180 days after <date date="1994-10-06">Oct. 6, 1994</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/103/349/s15">section 15 of Pub. L. 103–349</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t7/s2401">section 2401 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
